init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You decide to call the number.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You pick up the phone and dial the number.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It rings once, and then a voice comes on the line.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "The job I offered you," JFK replies.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're going to need a few things.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I'll send them over in the morning."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "The job I offered you," JFK repeats.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "A planet we're going to terraform and colonize.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're going to help me lead it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It's going to be a big job, and I'm going to need your help."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I'm going to need you to help me run the planet, and keep it safe."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I faked my death, and I've been working on New Earth for the last 4 years.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I've been working on it with the help of the best and brightest minds of our time.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're going to have to ask her yourself," JFK says.
